com.wm.xmldata.xmldocumenttype

Class XmlDataWorkspace

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wm.xmldata.xmldocumenttype.XmlDataWorkspace

  • public class XmlDataWorkspace
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a workspace in which XmlData Records and Fields can be accessed or created on an ad hoc basis. An XmlDataWorkspace is functionally equivalent to the collection of Document Types created in a single conversion step from a collection of XML Schemas (for example what happens when a Designer user creates a collection of XmlData Document Types from a schema). This collection is created in a namespace folder with various XML namespace components created in subfolders of the base folder. The intent is that these NSNodes should be functionally identical to those created by the XmlDataDocumentConverter. Their primary application is to work with the XmlDataMap and XmlDataCopy classes using either ad hoc Document Types or Document Types that have been created from a schema and already exist in a namespace. However, at present, ad hoc Document Types cannot reference Document Types that already exist in a namespace.

      • XmlDataWorkspace

        public XmlDataWorkspace()
        Create a temporary workspace. A temporary workspace has a transient namespace that is not persisted anywhere. It is strictly temporary and is typically used to create ad-hoc Document Types for use by XmlDtaMap, XmlDataCOpy,a nd XMlDataPath.
